# Ritual Magic

Combat spellcasting happens in seconds—instinctive reactions to immediate threats. But some magical effects are too complex, too powerful, or too permanent to accomplish in the heat of battle. These require ritual magic: extended casting that trades time and preparation for effects beyond normal spellcasting limits.

Ritual magic isn't a separate spell list. Instead, it's a casting method that lets spellcasters perform powerful effects when they have hours instead of seconds. The same spellcaster who hurls Fireballs in combat might spend an evening performing a ritual to create permanent magical wards, divine distant events, or contact otherworldly entities.

