## Understanding Ritual Casting

### Time vs. Power

Ritual magic's fundamental trade-off is time for power:

**Combat Spells:** Cast in seconds, last for rounds or minutes, affect immediate tactical situations. You cast Shield when attacked, Fireball when surrounded, Heal when wounded. These solve immediate problems through quick magical reactions.

**Ritual Spells:** Cast in hours, last for days or permanently, affect strategic situations. You perform rituals when you have time to prepare, when the magical effect needs to persist beyond combat, or when the magic required exceeds what combat casting can achieve.

The same spellcaster uses both approaches depending on circumstances. In combat, you cast quickly. Outside combat with time available, you perform rituals.

### Who Can Perform Rituals

Any character with Sorcery skill can attempt rituals, though success probability varies:

**Professional (+1) Sorcery:** Can perform basic rituals reliably. Success rates on standard rituals around 70-80% depending on attributes.

**Expert (+2) Sorcery:** Can perform complex rituals reliably. Success rates on difficult rituals around 70-80%.

**Master (+3) Sorcery:** Can perform even legendary rituals with reasonable success chances.

Untrained or Novice spellcasters can attempt rituals but face significant failure risks. Most ritual magic requires Professional or better Sorcery to perform safely.

### Ritual Components and Preparation

Rituals require more than just magical knowledge:

**Time:** Hours of concentrated casting, maintaining focus throughout the ritual period. Interruptions may ruin the ritual and waste invested time.

**Components:** Rare materials, symbolic objects, or sacrifices consumed during casting. More powerful rituals require more expensive components.

**Space:** Appropriate location—consecrated ground for divine rituals, ley line nexuses for arcane rituals, places with thematic resonance to the ritual's purpose.

**Assistance:** Complex rituals might require multiple spellcasters working in concert, each contributing their magical expertise to the combined working.

